SIMPLE: hydrothermal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hydrothermal
<hw>Hy`dro*ther"mal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydro-</ets>, 1 + <ets>thermal</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Of or pertaining to hot water; -- used esp. with reference to the
action of heated waters in dissolving, redepositing, and otherwise
producing mineral changes within the crust of the globe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>of, pertaining to, or using the hot waters or steam
found at special locations within the earth's crust; <as>as,
<ex>hydrothermal</ex> power generation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydrothorax</ent>⟦br⟧
